    <refnamediv>
        <refname>gluNewNurbsRenderer</refname>
        <refpurpose>create a NURBS object</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv><title>C Specification</title>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <funcprototype>
                <funcdef>GLUnurbs* <function>gluNewNurbsRenderer</function></funcdef>
            </funcprototype>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <!-- eqn: ignoring delim $$ -->
    <refsect1 id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            <function>gluNewNurbsRenderer</function> creates and returns a pointer to
            a new NURBS object.
            This object must be referred to when calling
            NURBS rendering and control functions. A return value of
            0 means that there is not enough memory to allocate the object.
        </para>
    </refsect1>
